conbody.p:
LogMiner requires an open database in ARCHIVELOG mode with archiving enabled. To
            determine the status of the database and enable LogMiner, use the following steps:

Log into the database as a user with DBA privileges.

Check the database logging
                        mode:select log_mode from v$database;
If the
                        command returns ARCHIVELOG, you can skip to Task 2.

If the command returns NOARCHIVELOG, continue with the following
                        steps:

Shut down the database:shutdown immediate;

Start up and mount the database:startup mount;

Configure enable archiving and open the
                    database:alter database archivelog;
alter database open;
